COVID-19 infections in Gauteng are increasing at an alarming rate. The high numbers have motivated the provincial government to call for a hard lockdown to curb the spread. To discuss this, eNCA speak to Gauteng Provincial Spokesperson, Thabo Masebe via Skype. Courtesy Dstv403 JOHANNESBURG - The Gauteng government says it is not calling for a return of a hard lockdown. READ: Motshekga also 'anxious' about her grandchildren returning to school This is according to Gauteng provincial spokesperson, Thabo Masebe following media reports suggesting that the province is considering imposing stricter regulations. "We are not calling for the return of hard lockdown. We fully understand and support the current risk-adjusted strategy, which is being implemented by the national government. READ: Karim on swine flu virus: No need for concern, for now "We understand that under Level 3, we had to reopen the economy and more sectors. The schools are reopening and we fully support that," said Gauteng provincial spokesperson, Thabo Masebe. Gauteng's COVID-19 infections are increasing at an alarming rate. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday. Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.